{"success": true, "message": "Fetched question.", "data": {"showTimer": true, "showAttemptInsight": true, "playSounds": true, "dontShowCorrectAnswerImmediately": false, "_id": "66bcc046ae81d148616b27fe", "type": "singleCorrect", "level": 1, "category": null, "approximateTimeRequired": 30, "imageBaseUrl": null, "helperText": null, "source": "1", "classes": [], "exams": ["615d76e4c52ffa3c944600e1"], "subjects": ["615d70f9a489afa3080ade2d"], "chapters": ["615d6ff12b295b085ab6ec0a"], "topics": [], "concepts": [], "microConcepts": [], "questionLabels": [], "previousYearPapers": [{"_id": "641b0e0e83941ec2736ade00", "title": "NEET 2022 (Phase 1)", "isVisible": true}], "question": {"text": "If a colour blind female marries a man whose mother was also colour blind, what are the chances of her progeny having colour blindness?", "image": null}, "options": [{"id": "M1mdH", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>50</mn><mo>%</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "cJWrE", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>75</mn><mo>%</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}, {"id": "ozlnO", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>100</mn><mo>%</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": true}, {"id": "gGIBb", "text": "<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>25</mn><mo>%</mo></math>", "image": null, "isCorrect": false}], "correctValue": null, "solution": {"text": "<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">Colour blindness is an X-linked disorder. For colour blindness to be effective, all X chromosomes within an individual must be affected, and since men only have one X chromosome and women have two, the chances of men being impacted are exponentially higher.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\">However, in this case, the mother is colour-blind and hence she carries X<sup>C</sup>X<sup>C</sup> genotype. Father&rsquo;s mother is also colour-blind and hence even she will be having the genotype as X<sup>C</sup>X<sup>C</sup>, and she will be transferring her X<sup>C</sup> chromosome to her son and hence, even the son will be colour-blind&nbsp;(X<sup>C</sup>Y). So, by this, we can tell all the X chromosomes are coding for colour-blind gene, and they inherit this gene to all their children,&nbsp;and hence, the chances of their child being colour-blind would be 100%.</p><p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://cdn-question-pool.getmarks.app/pyq/neet/414f4eb9-0371-456f-b4f2-9cb2ab861ae6-9739775.png\" style=\"width: 320px; height: 210px;\" /></p>", "image": null}, "videoSolution": null, "ques_type": "Single correct", "masterId": "MOGNEPYQ11631711", "numericalLowerLimit": null, "numericalUpperLimit": null, "bucket": "", "isRemoved": false, "cpyqbSubjects": ["616057290283de43c87e3e1a", "616057b00283de43c87e3e20", "64d50cd33df7f4a7f3017f71", "66b79bbbd4b564dfab4f94d2", "67fa60d64468eb1307ceb0b0", "6807d392647479b8e869647c"], "cpyqbChapters": ["616025d1b586ca3d904b80e6", "616025d0eb47b6e940bd7489", "64eb06d43118f713ecfef149", "66d58545a75f05ee8564f5d7", "67fdff3d378e1624ea7b6929", "68091fbc3a10446a207fda59"], "cpyqbExams": ["616059d70283de43c87e3e24", "616059730283de43c87e3e22"]}, "fetch_status": true}